\DOC ptrtype

\TYPE {ptrtype : (string -> string -> void)}

\SYNOPSIS
Creates a new pointer type.

\LIBRARY window

\DESCRIBE
{ptrtype `name` `type`} defines a new function
{newptr_name : void -> type pointer} which can then be used to create new 
pointers of type {type}.

Only works when the {compiling} flag is {true}.

\FAILURE
Never fails.

\SEEALSO
dispose, is_nil, store, value.

\ENDDOC
